Variable definitions for LJF -- force-decomposition

      Parameters:

namax			max # of atoms in group (row or col)
npmax			max # of owned atoms
nnmax			max # of neighbors per owned atom
nbmax			max # of total neighbor bins
ntmax			max # of thermodynamic calls

      Inputs:

dtstar			timestep (in reduced units)
ibin			binning flag - user-specified or default
ineigh			neighbor flag - N^2 or binning
inewt			Newton flag - Newton's 3rd law in neighboring or not
iseed			random number seed
itrans			transpose flag (2 kinds of force decomposition)
n[xyz]size		# of unit cells (fcc) in each dimension
nbin[xyz]		# of neighbor bins in each dimension
nneigh			reneighbor every this many steps
nstat			status calculation every this many steps
ntimes			# of timesteps
rc			inner force cutoff (in reduced units)
rhostar			requested density (in reduced units)
rs			neighbor cutoff (in reduced units)
tstar			requested temperature (in reduced units)

      Variables:

alat			lattice constant
bin(namax)		linked list pointers from one atom to next in bin
binpnt(nbmax)		pointers to 1st atom in each bin
binsize[xyz]		neighbor bin size in each dimension
conarr(ntmax)		conservation of energy
cutsq1			inner cutoff distance squared
cutsq2			outer cutoff distance squared
dt			timestep (in program units)
dtforce			timestep for velocity update with an extra factor
engarr(ntmax)		potential energy (in reduced units)
enginit			total energy at time 0
f(3,namax)		forces on group atoms (row)
fcopy(3,namax)		forces on other group atoms (col)
icol			column # of this node in force matrix (e.g. 0-31)
ierrorflag		error condition flag
irow			row # of this node in force matrix (e.g. 0-31)
itranrecv		transpose node # to recv positions from (send force to)
itransend		transpose node # to send positions to (recv force from)
mneigh			# of times neighbor routine called
mstat			# of times status routine called
natoms			total # of atoms
ncube			dimension of hypercube
neighmax		maximum # of neighbor
nend			where my atoms end in group (row)
ngbefore		# of atoms in all row groups before mine
nglocal			# of atoms in my group (row)
ngolocal		# of atoms in other group (col)
nlist(npmax*nnmax+nnmax) neighbor lists of atoms in my group
nlocal			# of atoms I own in group (row)
nnlist(namax+1)		pointers to start of neighbor lists of group atoms
node			my node #
noend			where my atoms end in other group (col)
nolocal			# of atoms I own in other group (col)
nostart			where my atoms start in other group (col)
nprocs			total # of processors
nstart			where my atoms start in group (row)
numcol			# of groups in column direction of force matrix
numcoldim		dimension of column direction
numrow			# of groups in row direction of force matrix
numrowdim		dimension of row direction
pntcopy(namax)		original (permuted) atom #'s of other group atoms (col)
prsarr(ntmax)		pressure (in reduced units)
sigma			LJ sigma (in program units)
sigsq			sigma squared
time_comm		time spent in communication
time_force		time spent in force routine
time_neigh		time spent in neighbor routine
time_total		total time for run
tmparr(ntmax)		temperature (in reduced units)
v(3,npmax)		velocities of owned atoms (row)
vec[1-10](10)		storage vectors for position/force communication
vold(3,npmax)		old velocities of owned atoms (row)
x(3,namax)		positions of group atoms (row)
xcopy(3,namax)		positions of other group atoms (col)
x[yz]mc			box size minus inner cutoff
x[yz]ms			box size minus outer cutoff
x[yz]prd		box size in each dimension (centered on 0.0)
x[yz]prd2		box edge in each dimension
